            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19458",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jordanryanmoore",
                        "name": "jordanryanmoore",
                        "displayName": "Jordan Ryan Moore",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Attaching patch that fixes this bug.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jordanryanmoore",
                        "name": "jordanryanmoore",
                        "displayName": "Jordan Ryan Moore",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-27T17:08:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-27T17:08:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19460",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've added a test for this in r8445.\n\nBut I cannot duplicate your issue.. can you produce a test to demonstrate the issue?\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-27T17:51:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-27T17:51:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19461",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jordanryanmoore",
                        "name": "jordanryanmoore",
                        "displayName": "Jordan Ryan Moore",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Change the line where the helper path is set in the test to the following:\n\n$view->addHelperPath(dirname(__FILE__) . '\/View\/_stubs\/HelperDir2', 'Zend_View_Helper');\n$view->addHelperPath(dirname(__FILE__), '');\n\nThis should duplicate the bug.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jordanryanmoore",
                        "name": "jordanryanmoore",
                        "displayName": "Jordan Ryan Moore",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-27T18:09:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-27T18:09:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19462",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Jordan,\n\nI added matthew to this issue to have a look.  It seems to me that having helpers without prefixes is not something i would consider \"Best Practices\".  I would ask Matthew to comment on that.\n\nOn another note, wouldnt the code:\n\n{code}\n\nclass Datetime\n{\n    \/* .... *\/\n}\n\n{code}\n\nThrow a fatal error about not being able to redeclare a class?\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-27T18:51:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-27T18:51:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19463",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jordanryanmoore",
                        "name": "jordanryanmoore",
                        "displayName": "Jordan Ryan Moore",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not defining DateTime as a class. I'm defining Zfe_View_Helper_DateTime, but since '' is a defined prefix for another helper path, it's finding a match for 'DateTime' there first, and ignoring my Zfe_View_Helper_DateTime.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jordanryanmoore",
                        "name": "jordanryanmoore",
                        "displayName": "Jordan Ryan Moore",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-27T18:58:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-27T18:58:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19734",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think ultimately, the use case you talk about: \"the ability to use helpers without a prefix\" is something that will continually get you in trouble since its hard to know what base classes will be included in php, and by other applications and\/or code.  I think the best thing to do is always use helper prefixes.\n\nAfter discussing with Matthew, I think that perhaps we should check to make sure a non-empty helper prefix is passed with all helper (and basePath) calls.\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-07T12:53:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-07T12:53:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19932",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=burkhard",
                        "name": "burkhard",
                        "displayName": "Burkhard Ritter",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have a related issue (should I file it as a new bug?):\n\nHelpers without a prefix do not work properly at all.\n\nAssume a Helper called FunkyHelper in a file FunkyHelper.php with the \"helper method\" \npublic function funkyHelper($a, $b, $c).  Zend_View_Abstract::getHelper($name) does a \"new $class()\", in this case \"new FunkyHelper()\" and FunkyHelper::funkyHelper() is called as a php4-style constructor. As funkyHelper($a, $b, $c) expects three parameters this results in an exception.\n\nThat's why I think empty helper prefixes should not be allowed. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=burkhard",
                        "name": "burkhard",
                        "displayName": "Burkhard Ritter",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-14T17:32:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-14T17:32:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19933",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Empty helper prefixes have been disallowed in 1.5.\n\nIn 1.6, the helper system inside Zend_View_Abstract will be replaced with Zend_Loader_PluginLoader (much like in Zend_Filter_Inflector as well as the usage you see in Zend_Form).  In general, not having a prefix is both a bad practice as well as confusing.  The naming structure we have (pseudo-namespaces\/PEAR naming conventions) is the only thing we have until php gets real namespaces.\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-14T19:38:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-14T19:38:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20424",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
